cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.NE, cs.SY 

The paper deals with information integration in a causal dynamical system, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-fields such as information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), systems and control (cs.SY), and neuroscience (cs.NE). The use of information geometry as a tool to quantify information integration further suggests that the paper may be relevant to the sub-field of statistical inference (cs.SI).
